Dear Team,

We are writing to inform you of updates to the company vacation policy
effective April 1, 2005.

Key changes:
- All employees now receive 15 days of paid vacation per year (up from 12).
- Vacation days can be carried over to the next year (up to 5 days maximum).
- Vacation requests should be submitted at least two weeks in advance.
- Emergency time off requests will be handled on a case-by-case basis.

Public holidays for 2005 are as follows:
- January 1 (New Year's Day)
- May 30 (Memorial Day)
- July 4 (Independence Day)
- September 5 (Labor Day)
- November 24 (Thanksgiving)
- December 25 (Christmas Day)

Please review the full updated policy document on the company intranet.
Contact HR if you have any questions or concerns.

